article.description: Stacey Bedell rushed for 100 yards and scored a career-best four touchdowns as Stony Brook rebounded to upset previously unbeaten Richmond in the conference opener for both teams Saturday.
article.headline: Bedell with 4 TDs, Stony Brook tops unbeaten Richmond 42-14
article.linkText: Bedell with 4 TDs, Stony Brook tops unbeaten Richmond 42-14
article.story: STONY BROOK, N.Y. -- Stacey Bedell rushed for 100 yards and scored a career-best four touchdowns as Stony Brook rebounded to upset previously unbeaten Richmond 42-14 in the conference opener for both teams Saturday. Richmond (2-1, 0-1 Colonial Athletic) came in as the second-ranked team in FCS polls and jumped ahead 7-0 on a Kyle Lauletta touchdown pass. But Bedell quickly put the Seawolves (2-1, 1-0) on top with a pair of TD runs and a 14-7 lead by the end of the opening quarter. His second score covered 49 yards. The Seawolves picked off Lauletta three times and held Richmond to 3-of-9 on third-down conversion attempts despite Lauletta's 411 yards passing. Sherman Alston Jr. opened the second half with a 96-yard kickoff return for a 28-14 Stony Brook lead. Brian Brown, with nine catches for 153 yards, notched his 14th 100-yard game and is within 71 yards of Richmond's career record for receiving yards.
